content:
Add the Broadcast Messages Tab to an App

If you’re using broadcasting in your standard SMS channel in Service Cloud, let your broadcasters view your company’s sent messages on the Broadcast Messages tab.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
This article applies to: Standard SMS channels
USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To view apps: View Setup and Configuration
To manage apps: Customize Application

Standard SMS channels are scheduled for retirement. To avoid service interruptions, upgrade your standard SMS channels to enhanced channels before February 14, 2026.

The Broadcast Messages tab displays the name, template, content, and number of recipients for each sent message.

Go to Setup | Apps | App Manager.
Open the menu next to a Lightning app, and click Edit.
In Lightning App Builder, click Navigation Items.
Select Broadcast Messages, and move it to the Selected Items list.
Click Save.

To confirm that Broadcast Messages was added to your app, open the app using the App Launcher.
title: Adding Broadcast Messages Tab in Service Cloud
